\begin_layout Plain Layout
https://microdata.worldbank.org/index.php/catalog/lsms
\end_layout

\end_inset

).
 Our quantitative model for the combined effect of wealth and consumption
 on one's status - which we use to describe the seemingly opposite effects
 of peer influences and poverty on status competitions - is aimed to be
 general enough to test the significance of status consumption across economies
 without relying on proxies of cultural contexts (e.g.
 consumer surveys etc.).
 In the sections that follow, Section 
