 Not only do the poor have insufficient income to increase their utility,
 they might also face the conditions of low intergenerational mobility (i.e.
 the opportunities for higher future wealth are generally limited to those
 who are already somewhat wealthy) - thus flocking in areas where bliss
 is lower (overall) compared to where the rich tend to live.
